text: m hi everyone local band here the
internet's busiest music nerd and it's
time for a review of this new cheek face
album too much to ask this is the third
full-length lp of california band
cheekface one of my most favorite new
finds over the past couple of weeks now
again this is their third lp so
obviously they've been at it for a
minute now but visiting their older
projects it's not like there's really a
night and day difference in terms of
sound and
style here it's kind of like cheekface
came to us fully formed already if
there's any notable differences on this
new lp it's that the band's performances
are getting tighter and the array of
influences going into their stuff is
getting wider from lofi indie rock to
power pop dance punk post punk a spritz
of pop punk as well topped with vocals
that range from exuberant shouts
amateurish cleans and
some very witty spoken word passages if
i had to boil the band's music down i
would say their appeal lies mostly in
very simple but sharp rock
instrumentation which they pull off with
a lot of energy as well as profoundly
absurd and clever song ideas like the
track we need a bigger dumpster which is
all about how situationally things can
snowball so quickly and how easily
people can adjust to the insanity and
just sort of sweep a problem under the
rug with descriptions of lighting a
match throwing it in the trash putting
the trash in a dumpster it's starting a
fire then needing a bigger dumpster to
contain the dumpster fire everything is
fine everything is fine something pretty
much like the coveted pandemic is
described in a similar way in the same
track and this is just the song's hook
on the verses they're packed with
restless lyrics to add to the tracks the
sense of hopelessness hopeless but uh
somehow the music comes across more
bubbly and sweet than you would expect
there's also featured singer which is a
hilarious and groovy bit of commentary
about becoming the featured singer on an
edm song the kind that is hated by djs
uh dance2 on tiktok and apparently spin

kind of sounds like lcd sound system but
somehow more tongue-in-cheek i feel so
weird describes a growing sense of dread
around everything feeling so odd the
vocal harmonies and close whispers of
weird on the chorus feel like i'm having
voices called to me in my head
descriptions of one's head guts and
heart being filled with barking dogs is
also a little off-putting and while in
one breath the lyrics give a peek into
the feeling of going insane there are
also thoughts penned into this thing
that seem like pretty everyday thoughts
in the mind of anybody who's uh
struggling in our modern day hellhole i
could get so much work done if i didn't
have to sleep anymore hard to
acknowledge something that's obvious
when it's really obvious and while i'm
feeling good i'm sure this at some point
will pass i also love how the track

of course when cheek face attempts a

but enjoyably so of course i'm talking
about the track next to me where we get
these strained refrains of i liked it
better when you were standing next to me
and between these hooks are the types of
lyrical images i would expect more from
a weird also talking about digging
through their trash and uh hollering yo
outside of their building at night and
being dubbed a yo guy as a result of
that cops are called there's a point
where his heart has a headache and he's

not corny or lazy in the way that some
comedy music tends to be as it still
works as a very fun diy pop rock track
and we go from insane devotion to a
complete lack thereof on the song
friends which is really about a
friendship that is hanging on by a
thread or really not much of a
friendship at all talking about the
various ways in which this friendship is
dysfunctional and how this other person
is sort of unlikable in that sense it's
a perfect parting ways song and cheek
face doing this track kind of reminded
me that there's really not enough of
these at least in a funny and amicable
way but societal commentary and focused
lyrics are not always this records bag
some moments on this lp revel in pure
absurdity whether that be in the series
of bars on pledge drive about a super
grain native to peru that is i guess
ruining the environment one of many
funny but strange lyrical detours across
this track the song election day has a
similar vibe to it with one of the
sweetest chord progressions across the
entire record which really fits the
acoustic direction of the instrumental
on this track dr bronner is called out
as uh not being a real doctor if that's
the case
how's that soap so good noodles is a
quick and chaotic interlude about a a
giant cup
of noodles even though part of me does
want more from this track especially in
terms of length
i do admire it for being able to add
levity to an already pretty silly album
meanwhile you always want to bomb the
middle east is not only insanely catchy
but has one of the strangest character
portraits i've heard on any record this
year seems like the point on this one is
to make as little sense as possible at
least on the surface i would say the
ending of this lp is just as strong as
the start the closing track vegan water
with its starry synths and driving dance
beats as well as refrains of i can do no
wrong is a pretty groovy and blissful
way to end things the lyrics fit the
bill in a very clever way though talking
about being so relevant or careless and
influential that you basically have no
accountability your friends aren't real
so you can do no wrong you're a
corporatist stage monkey so you can do
no wrong overall i'd say i enjoyed this
record a lot in fact i loved most of it
whole thing is a little scant a little
short of breath the brevity of some of
these tracks does leave me wanting a bit
more here and there some of the mixes on
these cuts are a little too rough around
the edges as well but still overall i
think cheekface is killing it here
handily one of the best rock records
i've heard in 2022 and no doubt you will
feel the same if you're looking for
something kind of fun silly a little
cheeky a little self-aware as well
feeling a strong seven to a light eight
